Phase 4: Analytics Dashboard

## Overview
Build an interactive analytics dashboard tab in the portal that visualizes initiative data with charts and summary cards.

## Summary Cards (top row)
- Total Initiatives count
- Total Yearly HC Saved (sum)
- Total Yearly USD Saved (sum, formatted as currency)
- Average Accuracy (%)
- Total Dev Time Hours (sum)

## Charts to Build

### 1. Initiatives by Program/Team (Bar Chart)
- X-axis: Program/Team names
- Y-axis: Count of initiatives
- Color-coded bars

### 2. AI Technique Distribution (Pie/Donut Chart)
- Segments: each AI Technique
- Show count and percentage

### 3. Status Pipeline (Bar Chart)
- X-axis: Developing, UAT, In Production
- Y-axis: Count of initiatives
- Color matches status tags (blue, orange, green)

### 4. Performance Metrics by Program (Grouped Bar Chart)
- X-axis: Program/Team
- Y-axis: Avg Time Saved %, Avg Cost Reduction %, Avg Accuracy %
- Three bars per program

### 5. Yearly USD Saved by Program (Horizontal Bar Chart)
- Y-axis: Program/Team
- X-axis: Sum of Yearly USD Saved
- Sorted descending

### 6. Submissions Over Time (Line Chart)
- X-axis: Month/Week
- Y-axis: Count of new initiatives
- Based on date_created field

## Technical Approach
- Use Chart.js via CDN (no build tools needed)
- Add backend aggregation endpoints:
  - GET /analytics/summary — totals and averages
  - GET /analytics/by-program — counts and metrics grouped by program
  - GET /analytics/by-technique — counts grouped by AI technique
  - GET /analytics/by-status — counts grouped by status
  - GET /analytics/trends — submissions over time (monthly)
- New "Dashboard" tab in the frontend, only visible to logged-in users
- Charts are interactive: hover for tooltips with exact values
- Responsive layout: 2 charts per row on desktop
